The paper deals with person identification using multiple modalities, including face, audio, and head features, which are all related to computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of deep convolutional neural networks (DCNNs) and machine learning methods also suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
